{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require leisure companies to provide exclusive Additional Learning Need sessions",
        "additional_details": "We think the number of exclusive sessions should be at least proportionate to the number of children and adults with learning difficulties. These opportunities could be published on a central database for parents/carers to access.\r\nWe think parents/carers should not have to rely on charities providing ad hoc opportunities.\r\n",
        "background": "We feel opportunities for recreation is extremely limited for those with learning difficulties in comparison to the more able. We think it should be a legal requirement that a business offering recreation to adults and children to offer regular, exclusive sessions suitable for ALN.",
